    <note>Chen(1) Xiang(6) [14225] See documentation for descendant, Yaozuo [98]. For possible linkage with the Jianning-&gt;Zhenjiang Chen(1), see documentation for Chen(1) Dayou(2) [21297], which suggests that Xiang(6) was a descendant of Fahui [21305] and that these were Wuxing Chen(1) descendants of the emperors of the Chen dynasty. However, since none of the funerary inscriptions for Xiang(6)'s descendants make this claim, I am assuming that all that Liu(2) Zai [11800] meant was that these were other important Song dynasty Chen ancestors of Chen(1) Jiayan [21309] (q.v.).</note>
